        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 5:51PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Champion, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
I-20 Near The Nolan-Mitchell County Line, Champion, Roscoe, Lake
Sweetwater, The Intersection Of Ranch Road 608 And Highway 147, Camp
Boothe Oaks, and Sweetwater.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 229 and 247.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
